FBIS3-51485 "drlat011_b_94010" FBIS-LAT-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 Inter-Caribbean Affairs St. Kitts and Nevis Eustace John Sworn in as Nevis Deputy Governor General FL1701181094 Bridgetown CANA in English 1510 GMT 17 Jan 94 FL1701181094 Bridgetown CANA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Basseterre, St. Kitts, 17 Jan, CANA -- A career civil servant, Eustace John, has been sworn as the new deputy governor general of Nevis. He succeeds the late Weston Parris, M.B.E. who died in office almost two years ago. John was sworn in by resident Puisne judge, Velma Hylton, in the presence of prime minister Dr. Kennedy Simmonds, Nevis Premier Vance Amory, family members, friends, and well wishers. The new deputy governor general is a former director of audit. He was also general manager of the state-owned ZIZ Radio and Television. John holds a certificate in Mass Communications from the Caribbean Institute of Mass Communications (Carimac) at the University of the West Indies (UWI) Mona Campus.
